"script": "Could you survive a nuclear blast by hiding inside your fridge? Picture the flash going off a mile away. For a heartbeat, the thick insulation shields you from the searing heat. But then the shockwave arrives, moving faster than sound. And your fridge, with you inside, becomes a metal box flung through the air like a thrown can. You'd tumble end over end, smashing into whatever's left standing. Even if the box held, the real killer is invisible. Radiation would already be soaking through the walls. So you might survive the bang, only to slowly fall apart from the inside over the next few days.",
